    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "Skimmer http://getskimmer.com is on a mission: to modernize the pool and spa service and repair industry. We’re a private equity-backed company with 6000+ customers using Skimmer’s pool service platform to transform their businesses. But we’re not stopping there (there are over 70,000 pool service companies in this surprisingly large “niche” space).\n\nOur customers love us almost as much as we love them (check out our reviews https://www.capterra.com/p/177014/Skimmer/reviews/ and our NPS score of 68!)\n\nWe were recently honored to join the Inc. 5000 list of fastest-growing companies, the Deloitte Fast 500, were named one of Built In Austin's Best Startups, as well as Austin's Best Places for Working Parents.\n\nWe’re looking for big thinkers with small egos, so let’s dive in!\n\nOur Values: At Skimmer we\n\n - Realize our customers' success is our success.\n\n - Build humble, diverse teams who have fun winning.\n\n - Drive results with urgency.\n\n - Earn trust through transparent communication.\n\nWho are you? / About You:\n\nSkimmer is looking for a player/coach technical leader for our Payments and Finance Development team. You will be responsible for leading a small team of developers and contributing code that improves our platform's operations around credit card processing, payment gateways, and financial integrations. You will report to the VP of Engineering and partner closely with Product, Finance, Customer Success,, and Support stakeholders.\n\nThe Payments and Finance Development Team owns all financial aspects of the Skimmer platform and mobile app, including credit card processing, payment gateways, and integration with accounting platforms. They own metrics like payment success rate, transaction security, and finance system data integrity. A separate team owns the Stripe integration for subscribing to Skimmer. This role owns the finance integrations that our customers use.\n\nYour number 1 goal in this role is to ensure a secure, reliable, and compliant payments and financial ecosystem.\n\nThe ideal candidate will have strong hands-on experience with API-based, real-time integrations, especially focusing on Stripe credit card processing and finance systems. As a player/coach, you will ensure technical excellence while leading a small team. Proficiency in leveraging AI tools to enhance team productivity and code quality is a significant plus. Your role is critical in ensuring secure, reliable, and compliant financial operations within the Skimmer platform.\n\nYou will be joining a company with a collaborative culture, focus on customers, and emphasis on having a good time together! 🏊\n\nWhat you'll do:\n\n - Lead and manage a small team of development engineers, acting as a player/coach to mentor and contribute technically.\n\n - Be the internal technical expert on Skimmer's payments and finance systems, including Stripe credit card processing.\n\n - Drive the integration and maintenance of financial and accounting platforms (e.g., QuickBooks Online) to ensure data accuracy and compliance.\n\n - Utilize AI tools and best practices to maximize the productivity and efficiency of your development team.\n\n - Assist in vendor selection for payment gateways and financial solutions.\n\n - Develop and implement secure, reliable APIs and systems for all payment and finance-related functionality.\n\n - Oversee security and compliance for payment card industry data (PCI DSS).\n\nEarly Projects (first 90 days):\n\n - Lead the migration or upgrade of our core Stripe credit card processing system to the latest API standards.\n\n - Scope and initiate the integration with QuickBooks Online or a similar accounting platform.\n\n - Review and enhance our current PCI compliance posture and data security protocols.\n\nYour Experience:\n\n - Experience in a technical leadership or lead player/coach role leading a development team’s prioritized workload at a SaaS startup.\n\n - Proven expertise building API integrations for SaaS products, specifically in the credit card processing and finance domain.\n\n - Deep, hands-on expertise with Stripe credit card processing and payment gateways.\n\n - Experience integrating with accounting platforms like QuickBooks Online, Xero, or similar .\n\n - Proficiency leveraging and implementing AI tools (preferably Claude) for development productivity.\n\n - Expertise developing in C# and proficient with Microsoft SQL.\n\n - Strong business acumen and an understanding of tax, accounting, and payment compliance (e.g., PCI DSS).\n\n - High emotional intelligence (EQ) and a track record of leading successful cross-functional projects.\n\n\nBENEFITS\n\n - Competitive base pay + bonus potential\n\n - Generous medical, dental, and vision plans (we pay 100% of your premium and 50% of your dependents’)\n\n - Fantastic culture with a very strong eNPS- we work hard, celebrate wins, and learn as we go to always be improving to benefit our customers.\n\n - Immediate access to 401(k) with company match\n\n - Flexible PTO (MINIMUM of 10 days required every year)\n\n - 12 weeks paid parental leave for birthing parent, 6 weeks paid leave for supporting partner\n\n - Remote work friendly\n\n - Comprehensive learning and development budget\n\n - A manager dedicated to your development\n\nAt Skimmer we are deeply committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace (it’s in our values). We’re proud to be an equal opportunity employer, seeking to identify and onboard people from all walks of life. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, family status, marital status, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, neurodiversity, disability, age, or veteran status, or any other non-merit based or legally protected grounds.\n\nWe also acknowledge that there is no “perfect” candidate - if you fulfill the majority  of these requirements, believe this is a role you would be excited about on a daily basis, and resonate with our culture, we encourage you to apply.",
